review_blob: This beer has become one of my all time favorites.  Rich, flavourfull.  Complex blending of flavours and great texture on the palate, but not overpowering.  Far too easy  a beer to drink

I was lucky enough to attend a beer dinner featuring Sound brewings beers and Monks Indiscretion was my favorite of the night.  Great nose with some floral hope notes, good mouth feel and flavour.  It became one of my top favorites that night.
